title: Sports Briefing | College Football: U.C.L.A. Player Arrested in Rape Case
text: College Football | Sports Briefing | College Football U.C.L.A. Player Arrested in Rape Case By THE ASSOCIATED PRESS Continue reading the main story Adam Searl, 20, a walk-on punter for No. 20 U.C.L.A. , has been arrested in a rape investigation, the Los Angeles police and university officials said. In October 2014, a U.C.L.A. student reported that she had awakened to find Searl sexually assaulting her after he had returned home with her after an off-campus party, the police said. A version of this brief appears in print on October 10, 2015, on page D7 of the New York edition with the headline: U.C.L.A. Player Arrested in Rape Case.
